This paper discusses Delay Tolerant Networks (DTNs) and their performance, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of spatio-temporal preferences and encounter statistics, which are related to social networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions routing protocols and their performance, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
